dal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bxp1665702896614.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bxp1665702896614.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bxp1665702896614.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bxp1665702896614\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SOAP Faults\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">SOAP messages are XML-based, and the SOAP protocol defines a SOAP Fault element for returning remote errors to the caller.\n </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">SOAP Fault Child Elements</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__1\">\n Element\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;faultcode&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__2\">\n Code that identifies the fault\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;faultstring&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__2\">\n A human readable explanation of the fault\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;faultactor&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__2\">\n Information about where the error was detected\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;detail&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bxp1665702896614__table_d3773e1_d3774e1_d3775e1__entry__2\">\n Application-specific error information related to the execution of the requested web service\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__p_d37565e1_d37566e1_d37567e1\">For detailed descriptions of the SOAP Fault elements, consult the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/2000/NOTE-SOAP-20000508/#_Toc478383507\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Simple Object Access Protocol (SOAP) 1.1</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__p_d37568e1_d37569e1_d37570e1\">If a SOAP fault is returned from a web service, the SOAP connector receives the fault and interprets it.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__section_zvr_njs_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d396766e149\">Example: SOAP Fault </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following XML shows an example of a SOAP fault:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"bxp1665702896614__pre_ks2_qjs_pcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;soapenv:Envelope\nxmlns:xml=\"http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace\"&gt;\n &lt;soapenv:Body&gt;\n &lt;soapenv:Fault&gt;\n &lt;faultcode&gt;fc:Server&lt;/faultcode&gt;\n &lt;faultstring lang=\"en-GB\"&gt;Bad error in server!&lt;/faultstring&gt;\n &lt;detail&gt;\n &lt;de1:detail1&gt;\n &lt;message&gt;Application-specific error 1&lt;/message&gt;\n &lt;e:error /&gt;\n &lt;/de1:detail1&gt;\n &lt;de2:detail2&gt;\n &lt;message&gt;\n &lt;e:error&gt;\n Application-specific error 2\n &lt;/e:error&gt;\n &lt;/message&gt;\n &lt;/de2:detail2&gt;\n &lt;/detail&gt;\n &lt;/soapenv:Fault&gt;\n &lt;/soapenv:Body&gt;\n&lt;/soapenv:Envelope&gt;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">As the example demonstrates, the structure of the detail element is\n            application-specific.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/opq1665702649630.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$procerrorcontext</a><p>Return the location of the error specified by $procerror.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526292\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526292\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SOAP Faults Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SOAP Faults SOAP messages are XML-based, and the SOAP protocol defines a SOAP Fault element for returning remote errors to the caller. Table 1. SOAP Fault Child Elements Element Description <faultcode> Code that identifies the fault <faultstring> A human readable explanation of the fault <faultactor> Information about where the error was detected <detail> Application-specific error information related to the execution of the requested web service For detailed descriptions of the SOAP Fault elements, consult the Simple Object Access Protocol (SOAP) 1.1 . If a SOAP fault is returned from a web service, the SOAP connector receives the fault and interprets it. Example: SOAP Fault The following XML shows an example of a SOAP fault: <soapenv:Envelope xmlns:xml=\"http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace\"> <soapenv:Body> <soapenv:Fault> <faultcode>fc:Server</faultcode> <faultstring lang=\"en-GB\">Bad error in server!</faultstring> <detail> <de1:detail1> <message>Application-specific error 1</message> <e:error /> </de1:detail1> <de2:detail2> <message> <e:error> Application-specific error 2 </e:error> </message> </de2:detail2> </detail> </soapenv:Fault> </soapenv:Body> </soapenv:Envelope> Copy As the example demonstrates, the structure of the detail element is application-specific. Related Links $procerrorcontext Return the location of the error specified by $procerror. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}